1
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:28,903
OK-DONG AND DONG-SEOK

2
00:00:31,781 --> 00:00:33,700
OK-DONG AND DONG-SEOK

3
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:01,019
Looking for something?

4
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:05,732
How much for 200?

5
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:07,067
-How many?
-Two hundred.

6
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:08,276
Two hundred?

7
00:01:08,359 --> 00:01:11,237
-Let me look around and come back.
-Okay. See you later.

8
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:16,785
Hey.

9
00:01:17,368 --> 00:01:19,746
You bought a lot.
Did you make a ton of money?

10
00:01:19,829 --> 00:01:21,706
-Do you need some?
-Yes, I do.

11
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:24,042
You know my number, right?
Text me your bank account number.

12
00:01:34,093 --> 00:01:36,054
Our specialty is doenjang stew.

13
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:40,058
I don't like doenjang stew.
Kimchi stew, please.

14
00:01:41,226 --> 00:01:43,603
Who doesn't like doenjang?

15
00:02:32,902 --> 00:02:36,489
How would you feel
if I suddenly showed up?

16
00:02:37,532 --> 00:02:40,660
Would you only be surprised?
Or would you be happy too?

17
00:02:40,743 --> 00:02:41,786
SEON-A

18
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,718
I'd be extremely happy.

19
00:03:00,972 --> 00:03:03,141
5 A.M.

20
00:03:03,224 --> 00:03:04,976
5 P.M.

21
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:06,561
SAVE

22
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:24,621
Ma'am.

23
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:26,706
Ms. Kang.

24
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:30,668
Ms. Kang, did you eat breakfast?

25
00:03:31,461 --> 00:03:34,047
Jeez. It's cold out.
Why did you leave this open?

26
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:35,965
I'm hot. Keep it open.

27
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:38,092
No, it's cold.

28
00:03:45,016 --> 00:03:46,267
What is all this?

29
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:48,102
Blankets.

30
00:03:51,272 --> 00:03:55,068
In-gwon bought me this last year.
Do you want it?

31
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:56,819
You can use it.

32
00:03:57,695 --> 00:03:59,030
Jeez.

33
00:03:59,113 --> 00:04:02,075
Why are you organizing
your blankets all of a sudden?

34
00:04:08,748 --> 00:04:11,292
I made some tasty beef soup for you.

35
00:04:12,001 --> 00:04:14,337
Have some broth. I'll reheat it for you.

36
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:18,299
But who are you calling?

37
00:04:19,384 --> 00:04:20,218
Dong-seok.

38
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:24,931
We need to go to Mokpo
for his late stepdad's memorial service.

39
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,432
Are you serious?

40
00:04:27,308 --> 00:04:29,269
Do you think he'd…

41
00:04:34,565 --> 00:04:36,567
Is he not picking up?

42
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,864
INCOMING CALL

43
00:04:46,577 --> 00:04:48,997
1 MISSED CALL

44
00:05:14,897 --> 00:05:17,859
-It's clean.
-I don't want it.

45
00:05:18,818 --> 00:05:20,153
I'll go heat up the soup.

46
00:06:06,074 --> 00:06:12,914
EUN-HUI

47
00:06:23,424 --> 00:06:24,842
Hey, Eun-hui.

48
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:27,261
Hey.

49
00:06:28,429 --> 00:06:30,515
Why aren't you picking up your mom's call?

50
00:06:30,598 --> 00:06:32,600
I don't have a mom.

51
00:06:35,436 --> 00:06:36,646
Where are you?

52
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:38,981
Come here right now.

53
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:41,109
I'm in Seoul to buy some goods.

54
00:06:41,192 --> 00:06:43,152
I was shopping until early morning.

55
00:06:44,987 --> 00:06:48,116
I'm going to bed.
See you on the market day.

56
00:06:48,199 --> 00:06:49,325
Your mom…

57
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:52,537
has cancer.

58
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,832
It's terminal.

59
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:10,096
So?

60
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:13,349
What kind of question is that?
Are you serious?

61
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:19,689
The doctor couldn't do anything.

62
00:07:20,982 --> 00:07:22,316
He gave up on her.

63
00:07:24,444 --> 00:07:25,736
Your mom seemed

64
00:07:27,447 --> 00:07:29,198
to have given up too.

65
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:32,285
She refused the surgery.

66
00:07:33,077 --> 00:07:34,662
It's too late to do anything now.

67
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:37,874
Her time is running out.

68
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:41,419
So come right now.

69
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:43,963
Don't regret this later.

70
00:07:46,799 --> 00:07:48,468
I'll just regret it later.

71
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:16,621
OK-DONG AND DONG-SEOK 1

72
00:08:37,099 --> 00:08:38,434
Hey, Dong-seok.

73
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:40,102
Well…

74
00:08:40,686 --> 00:08:43,606
I just got off work. I'm outside.

75
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:48,653
Dong-seok.

76
00:08:50,947 --> 00:08:52,657
-Hello?
-Mom.

77
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:55,243
Yeol!

78
00:08:58,037 --> 00:08:59,038
Yeol!

79
00:09:00,456 --> 00:09:01,582
I missed you!

80
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:08,631
-Did you miss me?
-A ton.

81
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:10,132
Me too.

82
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:11,926
He's been missing you a lot lately.

83
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:13,427
It wasn't easy to soothe him.

84
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:16,722
You must've missed me a lot.

85
00:09:16,806 --> 00:09:17,932
I did.

86
00:09:22,478 --> 00:09:24,355
-What should we have tonight?
-Pizza!

87
00:09:25,898 --> 00:09:27,817
We can't have pizza all the time.

88
00:09:28,818 --> 00:09:31,737
No pizza or fried chicken today.
We're having rice.

89
00:09:31,821 --> 00:09:33,239
Did you hear your dad?

90
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:36,409
No pizza. We're having rice for dinner.

91
00:09:36,492 --> 00:09:37,535
Okay.

92
00:09:43,207 --> 00:09:45,293
-Hey, watch out.
-I'm sorry.

93
00:09:45,376 --> 00:09:47,003
-It's okay.
-Be careful.

94
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:49,547
-Did he not cough today?
-No.

95
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:59,724
-Then who's that in that photo?
-He's my ex-boyfriend.

96
00:09:59,807 --> 00:10:02,018
Then why didn't you throw it away?

97
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,729
Because we could get back together.

98
00:10:04,812 --> 00:10:06,480
But you've already broken up.

99
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:28,377
Let's go.

100
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:30,463
Okay.

101
00:10:51,984 --> 00:10:53,527
EUN-HUI

102
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:13,089
SEON-A

103
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:15,675
POWER OFF

104
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:33,442
The number you are calling
is currently unavailable.

105
00:13:01,655 --> 00:13:03,324
MESSAGES
IN-GWON

106
00:13:03,407 --> 00:13:05,784
Hey, have you gone insane?
How can you call yourself human?

107
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:08,579
Your mother is dying,
yet you didn't even bat an eye.

108
00:13:08,662 --> 00:13:11,415
What a useless and impudent bastard.

109
00:13:11,499 --> 00:13:12,625
Call her.

110
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:14,919
MESSAGES
HO-SIK

111
00:13:15,002 --> 00:13:17,755
Dong-seok, where are you?
I'll come to you.

112
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:19,006
Where are you?

113
00:13:19,089 --> 00:13:20,257
MESSAGES
MS. HYEON

114
00:13:20,341 --> 00:13:23,093
I heard Eun-hui told you
that your mom was fighting cancer.

115
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:25,596
So why haven't you called your mom yet?

116
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:27,389
Call her.

117
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,266
MESSAGES
SEON-A

118
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:30,851
Why did you just leave that day?

119
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:34,730
You're not picking up either.
Call me back.

120
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:48,220
Are you dying tomorrow?

121
00:14:48,804 --> 00:14:50,306
Are you?

122
00:14:51,098 --> 00:14:52,933
Why would you suddenly ask Jeong-jun

123
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,811
to plow the field when he's busy?

124
00:14:57,897 --> 00:15:00,149
You're so weird.

125
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:04,028
Answer me. Are you dying soon?

126
00:15:05,362 --> 00:15:09,283
She always remains tight-lipped
and makes me frustrated.

127
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:11,368
Add more sesame seeds.

128
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:16,332
Look at you ordering me around.

129
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,132
Try it.

130
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,427
Am I your minion or something?

131
00:15:28,510 --> 00:15:30,054
Of course, you are.

132
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:35,100
It's tasty. Here.

133
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:41,649
It's too bland.

134
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:42,900
-Is it?
-Yes.

135
00:15:46,904 --> 00:15:48,238
This much?

136
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:57,164
-Try it again.
-I'm sure it's fine.

137
00:15:57,998 --> 00:15:59,208
Can I have some?

138
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:01,085
Take some yourself.

139
00:16:01,168 --> 00:16:03,462
Byeol-i, bring us some.

140
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:11,428
Here.

141
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,477
It's good. It's perfect.

142
00:16:21,188 --> 00:16:22,606
-It's good.
-Right?

143
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:25,401
-Give me some more.
-It's tasty.

144
00:16:26,944 --> 00:16:29,321
Ms. Kang, it's cold out. Go inside.

145
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,365
She likes the breeze.

146
00:16:32,157 --> 00:16:36,829
Jong-u and Jong-cheol should've prepared
the food for their dad's memorial service.

147
00:16:36,912 --> 00:16:39,957
Why do you have
to prepare everything and go there?

148
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,001
Plus, I'm too busy to go with you.

149
00:16:42,584 --> 00:16:47,006
That's enough. We volunteered to help her.
Are you trying to take credit?

150
00:16:47,673 --> 00:16:49,216
Don't do it if you're going to complain.

151
00:16:49,758 --> 00:16:51,010
Let me see it again.

152
00:16:51,719 --> 00:16:52,761
What?

153
00:16:53,762 --> 00:16:55,305
She can't stop watching it.

154
00:16:55,389 --> 00:16:58,017
She's already watched it
three times in front of us.

155
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,560
Pay me first.

156
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:03,522
Here.

157
00:17:06,108 --> 00:17:07,234
That's too expensive.

158
00:17:07,317 --> 00:17:08,652
No, it's not.

159
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:20,456
Grandma! I was right, wasn't I?

160
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,124
Dad's alive.

161
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,710
You were wrong.

162
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:27,004
I was right, wasn't I?

163
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:37,723
Dad asks if it's very windy there.

164
00:17:44,104 --> 00:17:46,190
He asks if you're healthy.

165
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:51,028
He says I'm being a good girl
and I even sing well.

166
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:55,365
He wants you to buy me some toys.

167
00:17:56,784 --> 00:17:59,411
Mother, the last part was a lie.

168
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:03,165
Dad drew this on me again.

169
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,501
UNITY

170
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:06,794
Eun-gi.

171
00:18:07,628 --> 00:18:12,257
Sing. Sing for Grandma.

172
00:18:14,259 --> 00:18:17,346
A chick can chirp

173
00:18:17,846 --> 00:18:20,557
A calf cries moo

174
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:21,642
Are you happy?

175
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:24,520
-A hunter can shoot…
-You've always been a good mother.

176
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:28,398
You're kindhearted.
That's why you're blessed.

177
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:40,494
Should I replay the video?
I won't charge you this time.

178
00:18:43,622 --> 00:18:46,750
A chick can chirp…

179
00:19:10,899 --> 00:19:14,278
Hey, why did you ignore my text?

180
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:16,363
Because it wasn't worth my attention.

181
00:19:17,781 --> 00:19:18,615
ABANG SUNDAE

182
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:19,867
Follow me.

183
00:19:22,494 --> 00:19:24,413
BANG FAMILY ICE

184
00:19:47,644 --> 00:19:50,355
PUREUNG

185
00:19:52,274 --> 00:19:55,402
CLOSED
IN PREPARATION

186
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:11,043
I'm not drinking. I need to drive.

187
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:12,794
Are you serious?

188
00:20:13,378 --> 00:20:14,588
Just drink it.

189
00:20:15,172 --> 00:20:18,175
I said, no. I don't want to.

190
00:20:19,426 --> 00:20:20,969
Just say it. I'm busy.

191
00:20:21,803 --> 00:20:23,347
How can you be busy?

192
00:20:24,264 --> 00:20:27,517
Shouldn't tending
to your mom be the priority?

193
00:20:31,897 --> 00:20:33,607
I'll drive your truck.

194
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,275
Why would you do that?

195
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:38,403
Say what you want to say.

196
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:40,155
Drive your mom to Mokpo.

197
00:20:41,448 --> 00:20:45,577
I was going to take some time off work
and drive her there myself.

198
00:20:45,661 --> 00:20:47,162
But she refused.

199
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:51,792
How can she go there by herself
when she can't even read the signs?

200
00:20:53,377 --> 00:20:54,253
Drive her yourself.

201
00:20:55,504 --> 00:20:57,047
Is that all?

202
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:00,968
I know how you feel.

203
00:21:01,677 --> 00:21:03,470
I know you're mad.

204
00:21:05,013 --> 00:21:06,181
Why would he be mad?

205
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:08,725
Why?

206
00:21:09,977 --> 00:21:13,772
Why would he be mad
about his mom fighting cancer?

207
00:21:14,898 --> 00:21:18,193
You should be heartbroken
and worried sick!

208
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:27,828
Do you not have a heart?
Not even an ounce of conscience?

209
00:21:27,911 --> 00:21:31,540
This is about your mom. She has cancer.

210
00:21:31,623 --> 00:21:35,252
And it's terminal, at that.

211
00:21:35,335 --> 00:21:38,672
You should rush over to her
and ask for her forgiveness.

212
00:21:38,755 --> 00:21:40,215
You should make up for the past.

213
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:42,926
What are you doing now?

214
00:21:43,010 --> 00:21:44,970
You're being stubborn and not picking up.

215
00:21:45,971 --> 00:21:49,725
Even we get heartbroken and teary-eyed

216
00:21:49,808 --> 00:21:51,852
if we think about
what she has gone through…

217
00:21:51,935 --> 00:21:53,854
You have no idea
what you're talking about.

218
00:21:55,355 --> 00:21:57,649
Just like how you regretted it
after your mom died,

219
00:21:58,525 --> 00:22:01,361
I'm going to do the same after mine dies.

220
00:22:01,945 --> 00:22:03,822
Okay? Can I go now?

221
00:22:04,990 --> 00:22:05,949
How dare you?

222
00:22:06,033 --> 00:22:09,328
Damn it. I ought to give you a beating.

223
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:11,079
As if I'll let you.

224
00:22:11,163 --> 00:22:12,289
You little…

225
00:22:13,165 --> 00:22:14,666
-Come on.
-Come at me.

226
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:17,044
Why are you taking off your clothes?

227
00:22:17,127 --> 00:22:19,796
-We didn't come here to fight!
-Sit down.

228
00:22:21,048 --> 00:22:22,924
Jeez, this is infuriating.

229
00:22:25,552 --> 00:22:26,803
Dong-seok.

230
00:22:29,097 --> 00:22:32,059
Do you think we're doing this
because we don't understand you?

231
00:22:35,145 --> 00:22:39,316
After your sister and my friend,
Dong-i, passed away,

232
00:22:42,027 --> 00:22:45,072
your mom remarried
and moved into another man's house

233
00:22:46,656 --> 00:22:50,577
less than a month afterward.
And I was truly upset.

234
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:53,330
I couldn't understand her.

235
00:22:54,539 --> 00:22:56,666
I'm sure you were
much more upset than I was.

236
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:01,213
I never told you this before.

237
00:23:04,257 --> 00:23:05,425
But I cried

238
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:08,970
day in, day out
because I felt sorry for you.

239
00:23:11,890 --> 00:23:13,225
But Dong-seok.

240
00:23:15,102 --> 00:23:16,353
Your mom…

241
00:23:19,815 --> 00:23:21,233
She can't eat anymore.

242
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:23,318
And she throws up blood.

243
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,364
I understand that you're mad.

244
00:23:28,532 --> 00:23:32,369
But what can you do, now that she's sick?

245
00:23:37,040 --> 00:23:38,291
Just give in.

246
00:23:39,584 --> 00:23:42,212
Do as she asks. Take her to Mokpo.

247
00:23:43,672 --> 00:23:45,340
And once she passes away,

248
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:49,344
you can put an end
to your ill-fated relationship.

249
00:23:51,429 --> 00:23:53,431
We'll help out with her funeral.

250
00:23:58,145 --> 00:23:59,479
I can't give in.

251
00:24:00,981 --> 00:24:02,190
I won't.

252
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:07,154
I'm not going to Mokpo.

253
00:24:09,781 --> 00:24:13,160
Dong-seok, I empathize with you.

254
00:24:13,952 --> 00:24:16,705
I truly understand how you feel.

255
00:24:17,205 --> 00:24:20,333
If we don't understand you, then who will?

256
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:24,171
I swear I completely understand you.

257
00:24:24,254 --> 00:24:25,839
-But--
-Don't say that.

258
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:31,428
Just say you don't understand me at all.

259
00:24:32,679 --> 00:24:35,182
Do you know what I hate hearing the most?

260
00:24:36,057 --> 00:24:37,851
Hearing that people understand me.

261
00:24:39,186 --> 00:24:40,520
You know nothing.

262
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:43,690
Have you ever seen your mom

263
00:24:44,232 --> 00:24:47,903
and your dad's friend,
who's also your friend's dad,

264
00:24:49,362 --> 00:24:53,366
go into the same bedroom together,

265
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:54,910
turn off the lights,

266
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:58,705
and sleep together?

267
00:25:04,377 --> 00:25:07,047
No, you haven't.
So what do you understand?

268
00:25:08,298 --> 00:25:10,008
Yeong-ok, give us bigger glasses.

269
00:25:11,509 --> 00:25:15,263
Do you know why
I've never considered getting married

270
00:25:15,347 --> 00:25:17,140
to the women I dated so far?

271
00:25:17,224 --> 00:25:18,183
My mom…

272
00:25:18,767 --> 00:25:23,605
I mean, because I was afraid that
they'd turn out to be like Ms. Kang.

273
00:25:24,940 --> 00:25:26,733
It doesn't matter how great they are.

274
00:25:26,816 --> 00:25:30,820
I feel disgusted if they resemble
my mom even in the slightest.

275
00:25:32,405 --> 00:25:34,616
You don't know what she did to me.

276
00:25:56,388 --> 00:25:58,848
You understand me? No, you don't.

277
00:25:59,641 --> 00:26:02,560
You don't fucking know anything.
You're just pissing me off.

278
00:26:19,035 --> 00:26:23,206
There must be something between them
that we're not aware of.

279
00:26:24,499 --> 00:26:27,335
You've done enough. You should let it go.

280
00:26:29,796 --> 00:26:30,839
All right.

281
00:26:34,342 --> 00:26:35,468
Eun-hui.

282
00:26:37,762 --> 00:26:39,014
Let's give up.

283
00:26:39,556 --> 00:26:41,016
It's not our business.

284
00:26:42,475 --> 00:26:43,977
Let's just drink.

285
00:26:55,530 --> 00:26:59,367
